snippet.textDisplay: Wow, just wow! I previously heard this on my laptop speakers and although it was GREAT,  I guess I wasn't fully immersed but OH MY GOD! I just heard this on a good speaker system and the levels these artists are able to reach is just mind blowing. I was and am speechless. I was brought to tears. What happened to Sabri Bhai is just a fn tragedy. The world lost something very valuable. These new singers are cool and all but what artists like Amjad and Rahat Bhai bring to the table is just irreplaceable. They showcase and bring out pieces of what we no longer have. They're the only links to their family, families who practiced generation after generation without ever having fame and money as their key motive. Music in it's self was their reward. That's something many people just can't fully understand and it's not their fault.

snippet.textDisplay:
If someone wants to learn how a mureed (disciple/follower) should respect and love his peer (master)...............just listen to the kalams of Hazrat Ameer Khusro (R.A). In rang / rung; performed by Fareed Ayaz & Abu Muhammad and Amjad Sabri & Rahat Fateh Ali.....you will see what happens when a person meets a Wali / Sufi Saint for the first time......... how it transforms his life and what is that experience, what a trans and what a transformation……. as he is totally absorbed into his peer, which is depicted by the glow….. the colour of Hazrat Nizamuddin Oliya (R.A). 

In Rang laaga; by sajjad Ali & Sanam Marvi……..the disciple expresses the highness of his master by talking about his superiority and connections and nearness to GOD and expresses his own humbleness that he is unable to reach those heights by himself and requests his master to hold his hands and take him along to the epic journey to reach GOD or Visaal (the meeting with GOD). 
Then the kalam Chaap Tilak by Abida Perveen & Rahat Fateh Ali: ..........which expresses the follower's extreme respect and his high regard for his master saint. His utmost faithfulness, his devotion to his master (in sufisim it is called fana fi sheikh and is a first step towards the ultimate objective of fana fi ALLAH)......... when he expresses that even if you don't look at me, even if you don't talk to me ........ I won’t be leaving your side...........I will be with you forever........and look…his eternal place is with his master at Dehli...... as if his wishes and prayers were answered by ALLAH(s.w.t).
